text: Khin Maung Myint also Maung Cho (; born 28 December 1951) is a Burmese politician currently serves as an Amyotha Hluttaw MP for Kachin State No. 9 constituency. He is a member of the National League for Democracy. ==Early life and education== He was born on 28 December 1951 in Katha, Sagaing Region, Myanmar. His previous job is jade trading. ==Political career== He is a member of the National League for Democracy. In the 2015 Myanmar general election, he was elected as an Amyotha Hluttaw MP, winning a majority of 30825 votes and elected representative from Kachin State No. 9 parliamentary constituency. ==References== Category:National League for Democracy politicians Category:1951 births Category:Living people Category:People from Sagaing Region
title: Khin Maung Myint (MP)
